SOC141-  Phishing URL Detected| EventID: 86 | Malicious | CLOSED|

Summary:
------------
On March 22, 2021, at 09:23 PM, the MSOC Security Team detected a phishing attempt flagged under rule SOC141 – Phishing URL Detected. The activity originated from workstation EmilyComp (IP: 172.16.17[.]49), associated with user ellie, who attempted to access a suspicious URL:

http://mogagrocol[.]ru/wp-content/plugins/akismet/fv/index.php?email=ellie@letsdefend[.]io

The request was directed to the external host mogagrocol.ru (IP: 91.189.114[.]8) and was made using a Chrome browser (User Agent: Mozilla/5.0, Chrome/79.0.3945.88). Despite being flagged, the device action indicates the request was allowed, meaning the connection to the phishing domain was not blocked at the time of detection.

I analyzed the URL using OSINT tools and in a sandbox environment. The URL was confirmed to be malicious. The suspicious activity involved a connection attempt to the domain mogagrocol.ru (91.189.114[.]8), specifically targeting a malicious PHP script hosted under a WordPress plugin path. The request contained the user’s corporate email address ellie@letsdefend.io as a query parameter.

This incident represents a successful connection to a phishing domain targeting an internal user. Immediate containment and remediation are required to minimize risk of further compromise, and network monitoring should be enforced to detect additional attempts. We have detected and quarantined the threat, noted the IOCs, and can now close the ticket.

 
